Genotype data were extracted from the UK Biobank for 14 candidate phenotypes and matched to corresponding GWAS summary statistics files obtained from the GWAS Catalog (\url{https://www.ebi.ac.uk/gwas/}). Quality controls were applied to both datasets independently. After initial heritability estimation, four phenotypes that did not reach nominal significance ($p > 0.05$) in the baseline GCTA model were removed, leaving 10 phenotypes for downstream heritability benchmarking and PRS evaluation.

