\subsubsection{GCTA-SBLUP}
GCTA-SBLUP requires a shrinkage parameter $\lambda$ computed from the heritability estimate. As shown in Equation~\ref{equation_lambda}, as the heritability estimate $h^2$ approaches 1, the shrinkage parameter $\lambda$ increases toward infinity, leading to maximum shrinkage of SNP effects. GCTA uses $\lambda$ together with the GWAS summary statistics and genotype data to compute shrinkage-adjusted SNP effect sizes $\hat{\beta}$ via Single-step Best Linear Unbiased Prediction (SBLUP):
\begin{equation}
\hat{\beta} = \left( \mathbf{G} + \mathbf{I} \lambda \right)^{-1} \mathbf{X}^T \mathbf{y}
\end{equation}

